 ago. Vanguard News Nigeria Google faced a record EU fine Wednesday for using its Android smartphone system to illegally boost its search engine, in a ruling that risks a fresh clash between Brussels and Washington. July 18, 2018 In "Technology" Google, the world’s most popular internet search engine, has been slammed a record $2.7 billion fine by Europe’s anti-trust agency over foul play in in dominating searches and smartphones. The fine signalled a tough stance by the agency in the first of three investigations into the company’s dominance in searches… June 27, 2017 In "News" Google celebrated its 20th birthday Monday, marking two decades in which it has grown from simply a better way to explore the internet to a search engine so woven into daily life its name has become a verb. September 24, 2018 In "Technology"